**WHO's Work on Prevention and Control of Non-Communicable Diseases Focuses on Strengthening Health Systems**

The World Health Assembly recently endorsed a resolution strongly emphasizing the strengthening of health systems. The prevention and control of diseases play a crucial role in ensuring the well-being of populations and reducing the highest burden of disease that people can experience. It also supports maternal and child health and respects the right to work and the right to education. This resolution aims to guide the actions of actors in prevention by:

*   Integrating prevention into health programs and addressing health determinants and inequalities, allocating resources, and promoting innovation and technology adoption;
*   Ensuring that countries have the resources to respond effectively to the prevention of diseases using digital health technologies due to disease challenges;
*   Ensuring that people in vulnerable situations and those at high risk benefit from the essential services of prevention, which are accessible, affordable, and sustainable, using digital health technologies;
*   Addressing the digital divide for people to benefit from prevention services and digital health technologies that can cause financial hardship; and
*   Improving the capacity of prevention workers to serve the needs of urban populations.

