"At 2:00pm CEST, following a family photo with the Government Advisory Board, the high-level briefing of the Assembly will be broadcast from the Palais des Nations featuring remarks from the WHO Secretary-General, Heads of State, and key ministers. (List of speakers below). During this session, the DG will present awards for lifetime achievement to two global health leaders. On Thursday, 22 June, the Secretary-General will deliver his address in detail at 10:00am. On Tuesday, 26 June, representatives of all six global health pillars will join the WHO Secretary-General to present twelve health awards and prizes for seven individuals for the year 2023. They are coming from Bahrain, China, Guatemala, Lebanon, Nepal, Thailand, and the Philippines.

**Key Issues Being Addressed:**

*   Review of WHO’s work in health emergencies, in relation to the Global Health Regulations and strengthening WHO’s preparedness for and response to health emergencies;
*   Global strategies and progress on areas such as women’s and children’s health, disability, universal health coverage, primary health care, prevention and control of non-communicable diseases, essential medicines and vaccines, neglected tropical diseases, mental health and substance use, road safety and violence prevention;
*   Drafting of the WHO Medium-Term Plan for 2024-2025, including decisions on the allocation of funds reviewed by the Board and other matters arising from the Expert Advisory Group on the Strategic and Plan Implementation. "
